==Introduction==
The default approach to create new pages after clicking on the [[Image:Concept Add Icon.png|20px]] '''Add new''' button is a three phases processes:
* Step 1. user is asked for a page name in a one line input field ('''user might enter any value''')
* Step 2. after clicking "Create or Edit" button user is redirected to the "Edit Form" where he can provide all data entity details
* Step 3. after clicking on "Save" button the page with the name provided in Step 1 and details provided in Step 2 is created.


This above approach can be modified by the following mechanisms:
;Formal definition of the page naming schema
The page naming schema might be represented using formal Regex expressions.
Upon opening the Edit Page (Step 2 in above process or after clicking on "Edit with form"),
or the View Page, system verifies if the actual page name follows that format.
If a check is negative a warning message is displayed in the top part of the page
and user is recommended to change the name of the page.

;Automatic page name assignment
The Wiki Model can define the naming schema which should be automatically followed when a new page is created.
The naming schema string can mix:
:* static text fragments (e.g. ' Applications', Test Case ', ' @ ')
:* references to the Concept Properties in the brackets (e.g. '{Is lead by}', '{Is tested during}')
:* automatically assigned sequence number ('[AUTOINDEX])

In this approach the processes is simplified. Upon clicking on the [[Image:Concept Add Icon.png|20px]] '''Add new''' button, user is redirected straight to the 'Edit Form'
to provide data entity values. Upon saving the page the automatic page name assignment string is processed and final page name derived.


==Definition==
<pre>
<concept name="{CONCEPT}">
  <nomenclature nameschema="{PAGE NAME SCHEMA}" autopage="{AUTO PAGE NAME SCHEMA}">{PAGE NAME NOMENCLATURE}<nomenclature>
  ...
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {CONCEPT}
| A short name of the Concept.
|-
! {PAGE NAME NOMENCLATURE}
| A short, informal description of the rules governing name page conventions for this Concept
|-
! {PAGE NAME SCHEMA}
| A formal Regex expression to define the naming format of the pages. If {AUTO PAGE NAME SCHEMA} is defined the Regex expression will be derived from the auto page name schema definition.
|-
! {AUTO PAGE NAME SCHEMA}
| A formal naming schema to be followed by automatically assigned page names.
The schema string can mix:
:* static text fragments (e.g. ' Applications', Test Case ', ' @ ')
:* references to the Concept Properties in the brackets preceded with $ (e.g. '${Is lead by}', '${Is tested during}')
:* automatically assigned sequence number ('[AUTOINDEX:{NUMBER}]), where {NUMBER} represents the starting value of the sequence
Note that the properties used in the naming schema must be marked as 'mandatory'.
|}


==Semantic database==
The rules described in this page govern the page names stored in the database.


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="Enclave">
  <nomenclature nameschema="/(.+?) Enclave$/">All pages should end with "Enclave" suffix</nomenclature>
</concept>
</pre>
The Enclave page names will have to end with "Enclave" phrase.

<pre>
<concept name="Enclave">
</concept>

<concept name="Site">
  <nomenclature autopage="${Title} (${Is part of})">The page name is automatically assigned and follows the pattern {TITLE} ({ENCLAVE})</nomenclature>
  <structure>
    <property="Title" mandatory="true"/>
    <property="Is part of" refersTo="Enclave" mandatory="true"/>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>
The Site page names will be assigned automatically and will follow the "City (Enclave)" pattern: "Bydgoszcz (CFBL)".

<pre>
<concept name="Test Case">
  <nomenclature autopage="Test Case [AUTOINDEX:00001]@${Is tested at}">The page name is automatically assigned and follows the (Test Case 00004@Event) pattern: "Test Case 0004@CWIX 2017"</nomenclature>
  <structure>
    <property name="Description"/>
    <property name="Is tested at" refersTo="Event" mandatory="true"/>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>
The Test Case page names will be assigned automatically and will follow the (Test Case 00004@Event) pattern: "Test Case 0004@CWIX 2017"


